00:00:06.359 --> 00:00:09.510
as unit test. There is very subtle

00:00:09.510 --> 00:00:12.210
difference here so if you want to do

00:00:12.210 --> 00:00:14.639
unit test you will mock so if you are

00:00:14.639 --> 00:00:16.440
mocking that means we are still using

00:00:16.440 --> 00:00:18.570
spring injection through the

00:00:18.570 --> 00:00:19.949
configuration that way we are making

00:00:19.949 --> 00:00:21.689
sure that we have wired the beans and

00:00:21.689 --> 00:00:24.150
everything properly at the same time we

00:00:24.150 --> 00:00:25.619
are not going to call into the real

00:00:25.619 --> 00:00:28.529
DAO's the real next layer we are still

00:00:28.529 --> 00:00:31.619
mocking it so it is still a unit test we

00:00:31.619 --> 00:00:33.660
could have got away without doing all

00:00:33.660 --> 00:00:35.730
this spring stuff but here we are verifying

00:00:35.730 --> 00:00:37.469
that everything we are

00:00:37.469 --> 00:00:39.090
configuring or all the dependency

00:00:39.090 --> 00:00:40.829
injection we are doing with spring is

00:00:40.829 --> 00:00:43.110
still intact it's a great way of testing

00:00:43.110 --> 00:00:46.079
the dependency injection as well but if

00:00:46.079 --> 00:00:48.270
you don't mock here if you don't use

00:00:48.270 --> 00:00:50.309
